<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000019#     2#       368.18#">Va. Code Ann. § 19.2-368.18</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_19.2-368.18"/><heading><desig>§ 19.2-368.18.</desig><title>Criminal Injuries Compensation Fund</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> There is hereby created a special fund to be administered by the Comptroller, known as the Criminal Injuries Compensation Fund.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Whenever the costs provided for in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.1">§§ 17.1-275.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.2"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.2">17.1-275.2<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.2#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.3"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.3">17.1-275.3<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.3#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.4"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.4">17.1-275.4<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.4#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.7"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.7">17.1-275.7<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.7#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.8"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.8">17.1-275.8<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.8#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 17.1-275.9"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 17.1-275.9">§ 17.1-275.9<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000017#     1#        275.9#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or subsections B or C of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 16.1-69.48:1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 16.1-69.48:1">§ 16.1-69.48:1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#958#0000000016#0000000001#     69.48#0000000001#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> are assessed, a portion of the costs, as specified in those sections, shall be paid over to the Comptroller to be deposited into the Criminal Injuries Compensation Fund. Under no condition shall a political subdivision be held liable for the payment of this sum.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> No claim shall be accepted under the provisions of this chapter when the crime that gave rise to such claim occurred prior to July 1, 1977.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d"/><heading><desig>D.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Sums available in the Criminal Injuries Compensation Fund shall be used for the purpose of payment of the costs and expenses necessary for the administration of this chapter and for the payment of claims pursuant to this chapter.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_e"/><heading><desig>E.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> All revenues deposited into the Criminal Injuries Compensation Fund, and appropriated for the purposes of this chapter, shall be immediately available for the payment of claims.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1976, c. 605; 1978, c. 413; 1980, c. 521; 1985, c. 230; 1988, c. 748; <citation normalizedCite="1993 VA CH 434"><content><span normalizedCite="1993 Va. Ch. 434">1993, c. 434<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1993#000434#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1996 VA CH 760"><content><span normalizedCite="1996 Va. Ch. 760">1996, cc. 760<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1996#000760#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1996 VA CH 976"><content><span normalizedCite="1996 Va. Ch. 976">976<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1996#000976#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2002 VA CH 831"><content><span normalizedCite="2002 Va. Ch. 831">2002, c. 831<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2002#000831#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http: